Problem 2

The data for Problem 2 is the Fertility data in the AER package. This data is from the 1980 US Census and is comprised of date on married women aged 21-35 with two or more children. The data report the gender of each womans first and second child, the womans race, age, number of weeks worked in 1979, and whether the woman had more than two children.

There are four possible gender combinations for the first two Children. Product a plot the contracts the frequency of these four combinations. Are the frequencies different for women in their 20s and wemen who are older than 29?

It is clear that there are differences in frequency between two age groups.

Produce a plot that contrasts the frequency of having more than two children by race and ethnicity.
